2. Third-party lore and source material

This repository preserves and organizes public lore, quotations, posts,
scrolls, URLs, and other source material that may have been authored or owned
by Toadgod, Tobyworld participants, community members, platforms, or other
third parties.

ToadAid does not claim ownership of third-party source material and cannot
license rights it does not own. Inclusion in this repository does not change
the original ownership, copyright, trademark, platform terms, or other rights
that may apply to that material.

Users are responsible for determining whether their intended reuse of
third-party material is permitted by the relevant rights holder and applicable
law. Where a record identifies an author, source, URL, date, or other
provenance, those details must be preserved.

3. Corpus compilation and provenance framework

To the extent ToadAid holds rights in the selection, organization, metadata,
annotations, provenance model, classifications, source identifiers, and
compilation structure of this corpus, ToadAid grants permission to use,
reproduce, adapt, and integrate those elements, including in Gemini Gems,
ChatGPT GPTs, agents, applications, research tools, and community archives.

This permission is conditioned on the following:

- Preserve source IDs, authorship, dates, URLs, classifications, and provenance
  boundaries where present.
- Keep direct source quotations distinguishable from summaries,
  interpretations, annotations, and model-generated inferences.
- Do not present community interpretation or model output as an original
  statement by Toadgod or another source author.
- Do not claim that ToadAid owns, controls, endorses, or officially represents
  Tobyworld.
- Do not remove notices identifying third-party ownership or uncertain rights.
- Clearly mark corrections, cancellations, later status updates, and unknown
  or disputed claims.

4. Suggested attribution

When using the corpus compilation or provenance framework, use a reasonable
credit such as:

“Powered by the ToadAid Lore Guardian corpus and provenance framework.”

When reproducing an individual source record, also preserve the record's
identified source author and provenance information where available.

5. No endorsement, warranty, or financial advice

Permission to use this repository does not imply endorsement by ToadAid,
Toadgod, Tobyworld, or any source author.

The repository is provided “AS IS”, without warranties or conditions of any
kind, express or implied. It is an archival and agent-building resource, not
financial, legal, or investment advice.

6. Conflicts and record-specific notices

A file-level or record-level rights notice controls over these general terms
for that specific material. If the ownership or reuse status of a source is
uncertain, treat the source as third-party material with no additional rights
granted by ToadAid.
